<number box="[804,857,1393,1419]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.5">1.50</number>
± 
<number box="[896,967,1393,1419]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.235">0.235</number>
); dorsal ridge absent; ventral ridge reaching the mid­point of the genital capsule (
<number box="[884,1036,1433,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.05" valueMax="0.06" valueMin="0.04">0.04 ± 0.06</number>
); ventral ridge length to basal distance (
<number box="[442,495,1473,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.42">0.42</number>
± 
<number box="[525,596,1473,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.046">0.046</number>
); basal distance to genital capsule length (
<number box="[1087,1140,1473,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.77">0.77</number>
± 
<number box="[1170,1241,1473,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.014">0.014</number>
); intervolsellar process long with pointed apex attaining same level or extending slightly beyond apex of dorsal lamina; ventral processes at base of intervolsellar process. Quantitative data were obtained from three males.
</paragraph>
